At the time of the incident, I was an 18-year-old high school student who longed for a beautiful dress to wear to prom. Unfortunately, I was well aware that I did not have the means to afford such an extravagant purchase. However, I deeply regret allowing my desire for the dress to cloud my judgment, leading me to make this one-time mistake.

I want to emphasize that this incident does not reflect my true character or intentions. Prior to this regrettable incident, I had never been involved in any criminal activities. Throughout my young adulthood, I have consistently sought to maintain a good reputation and make positive contributions to society.

Becoming a nurse has been my long-standing dream after high school. My passion to help others and provide care to those in need has inspired me to pursue this noble profession. I am genuinely committed to personal growth and dedicate myself to becoming a responsible member of society.

Your Honor, I assure you that I am determined to learn from this experience and make every effort to rectify my mistake. I humbly accept any punishment deemed appropriate by the court, as I understand the importance of accountability and rehabilitation.

Thank you for considering my plea, Your Honor. I ask for your mercy and understanding as I strive to demonstrate genuine remorse, personal growth, and my unwavering commitment to becoming a compassionate nurse and valuable member of society.

